benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search - Search custom fields by type, name and optional value

covered: Valid Request: Numerous scenarios validate successful GET with various query parameters (objectType, fieldName, fieldValue, combinations).
Empty Response: Tests include fetch all (TC01) and empty DB state (TC28).
Query Parameters: Multiple combinations tested (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC12, TC15, TC16, TC37).
Pagination: Pagination scenarios present (TC07, TC21, TC31).
Error Handling/Invalid Input: Tests for invalid objectType (TC13), invalid offset (TC14), invalid limit (TC15), invalid audit (TC16), SQL injection (TC19), XSS (TC20).
Resilience/Recovery: Recovery from transient network failure (TC36).
Data Integrity/Integration: Tests around audit FULL and integration with audit service (TC32, TC33).
Regression/Backward Compatibility: Regression tests (TC25, TC27, TC28).
Edge Cases: Very large limit/offset tests (TC21, TC22).
Documentation/Accessibility: API documentation accessibility (TC34), descriptive error messages (TC35).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No explicit tests validating rate limiting or throttling behavior under bursts.
Caching Behavior: No tests asserting caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache invalidation.
Authorization Variants: Only 401 on missing auth is covered; no explicit 403/insufficient-permissions scenarios.
Edge-case Performance under heavy load with explicit SLA checks beyond TC30/TC31; no detailed thresholds beyond general time assertions.
Strict 403/401 combinations for role-based access control are not explored (e.g., authenticated but forbidden).
recommendations: Add explicit rate-limiting/throttling tests to verify behavior under bursts and to confirm retry-after or similar hints.
Add tests asserting caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and behavior when data changes (cache invalidation).
Extend authorization coverage to include forbidden/insufficient-permission cases (403) and role-based access variations.
Introduce more explicit performance tests under concurrent load with measurable SLA thresholds beyond generic timings (e.g., under peak load with defined p95 latency).
Consider a dedicated test for handling invalid/malformed query parameter combinations that could interact (e.g., objectType with invalid fieldName) to ensure robust input validation.
